sentences.sContent: We filmed there this summer, and it is deeply touching to see that Collins not only ran a rare, uncorrupt and democratic camp, but had put up a schoolhouse, a library and a meeting hall.
sentences.sContent_eng: We filmed there this summer, and it is deeply touching to see that Collins not only ran a rare, uncorrupt and democratic camp, but had put up a schoolhouse, a library and a meeting hall.
sentences.sCn: 今年夏天我们在那里拍摄时，激动地发现，科林斯不仅管理着一个少见的、廉洁民主的营地，并且建设了校舍、图书馆和大会堂。

synos.tran: 不腐败的；未堕落的；无讹误的；纯正的
